            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;I&apos;m staring at 2,000 lines of if statements because the previous dev didn&apos;t use square brackets, and statically accessed object properties by dot notation. It&apos;s for an approval process app that has 7 different approvers and the steps are all the same. /rip&lt;/span&gt;

