                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment118398120_52197878&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2021-04-07 07:18:13Z, License: CC BY-SA 4.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Apr 7, 2021 at 7:18&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;It&apos;s best to avoid using &lt;code&gt;eval&lt;/code&gt; whenever possible. &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/86513/why-is-using-the-javascript-eval-function-a-bad-idea&quot; title=&quot;why is using the javascript eval function a bad idea&quot;&gt;stackoverflow.com/questions/86513/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/1766230/luke&quot; title=&quot;16,956 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Luke&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment50047460_30974910&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2015-06-23 18:07:53Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Jun 23, 2015 at 18:07&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Using &lt;code&gt;eval&lt;/code&gt; for something as trivial as accessing properties is plain overkill and hardly advisable under any circumstance. What&apos;s &quot;trouble&quot;? &lt;code&gt;obj[&apos;nested&apos;][&apos;test&apos;]&lt;/code&gt; works very well and doesn&apos;t require you to embed code in strings.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/4174897/kyll&quot; title=&quot;7,039 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Kyll&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment54398689_30974910&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2015-10-23 10:14:34Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Oct 23, 2015 at 10:14&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;

            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;eval is three times slower or more, I wouldn&apos;t recommend this to newbies because it might teach them bad habits. I use &lt;code&gt;obj[&apos;nested&apos;][&apos;value&apos;]&lt;/code&gt; - remember kids, eval is evil!&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/1564919/jaggedsoft&quot; title=&quot;3,557 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;jaggedsoft&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment55619232_30974910&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2015-11-26 01:25:45Z, License: CC BY-SA 3.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Nov 26, 2015 at 1:25&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
                        &lt;span title=&quot;this comment was edited 1 time&quot;&gt;
