&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m trying to access a property of an object using a dynamic name. Is this possible?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-js s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-javascript&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; something = { &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-attr&quot;&gt;bar&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&quot;Foobar!&quot;&lt;/span&gt; };
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-keyword&quot;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; foo = &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-string&quot;&gt;&apos;bar&apos;&lt;/span&gt;;
something.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-property&quot;&gt;foo&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;// The idea is to access something.bar, getting &quot;Foobar!&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
